# Git Workflow — Mandatory

## Per Task

1. `git checkout main && git pull`
2. Create branch: `task/X.Y-short-description` (see TASKS.md)
3. Implement only that task's acceptance criteria
4. Run tests/lint before commit
5. Commit with conventional message: `feat(scope): description`
6. `git push -u origin <branch>`

## Per Phase

1. Merge task branches into phase branch (e.g. `phase-1/core-agent`) via PR
2. When phase acceptance criteria met, open PR: `phase-N → main`
3. PR title matches TASKS.md (e.g. `feat: LangGraph supervisor and Groq LLM integration`)
4. Merge to `main` only after CI passes (once CI exists)

## Never

- Force push to `main`
- Skip hooks unless user explicitly requests
- Commit `.env` or API keys
- Bundle unrelated tasks in one commit

## Update TASKS.md

Mark completed tasks `[x]` and add PR link in the progress table when merging.
